          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Target foils were placed between ultrapure (99.9999%)",
                "silver catcher foils which served to collect",
                "recoiling fission fragments in the forward and",
                "backward (to the beam) directions. The uranium foils",
                "had been analyzed both spectroscopically and",
                "radiochemically for some 54 elements which might",
                "produce spallation products that could possibly",
                "interfere with the fission fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Standard chemical procedures using",
                "carrier techniques were used to separate the various",
                "fission products. After irradiation, the target and",
                "the catcher foils were removed and dissolved",
                "separately in the presence of added carriers. One of",
                "the problems encountered in this investigation was to",
                "find satisfactory radiochemical procedures capable of",
                "separating the trace amounts of radioactivity due to",
                "ternary-fission nuclides from gross amounts of binary",
                "and spallation products. The activities were counted",
                "in suitable chemically stable precipitates in Geiger",
                "counters provided with anticoincidence guard counters."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The resolution of the decay curves was aided",
                "by a modified Los Alamos PAKAG IBM 7094 computer",
                "program. In computing the absolute cross sections for",
                "the recoil products Si31, Mn56, and Ni66, the",
                "assumption was made that the same fraction of the",
                "total activity recoiled out of the thick uranium",
                "target as was experimentally found for Mg28 and Sr89",
                " (7% in both the forward and backward direction in",
                "each case)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections are only necessary to the lower-energy",
                "data (<25 MeV) and were made using the known cross",
                "sections and an activation analysis of the uranium",
                "for aluminum and magnesium content."
              ]
            }
          ],
